features: High-quality material: This blade is made of high-quality 30Cr13 stainless steel, high hardness, sharp blade, corrosion-resistant and not easy to rust, safe and health.
Sharp Edge: When cooking, the sharpness of your knife is the key to getting the best cuts. The blade is sharp and will not slip when cutting things to ensure your safety.
MULTI-PURPOSE: This knife is ideal for slicing fruits, vegetables, and meat, as well as tough tasks like peeling, chopping, and removing meat above the bone.
Comfortable and non-slip ergonomic handle: Ergonomically designed for optimal comfort, control and agility, the handle is not easy to slip even if it gets wet.

Lightweight and not easy to stick: The blade is light and light, and it is not easy to get tired after holding it for a long time. The groove design on the knife surface prevents you from sticking when cutting things. Let you enjoy the fun of cooking.
body.description: With blade cover: dustproof and breathable, protect the blade and protect your safety. The hollow blade cover design allows the blade to dry quickly even if it is placed in a blade cover. Tips: 1.After the knife is used, wash it with clean water, and then dry it with a cloth or paper towel, which can better extend the service life of the knife. 2.Do not use hard tools such as steel wire balls for cleaning to avoid scratching the surface. 3.After using the knife, please put it in the knife cover in time and keep it out of the reach of children. 4.The blade is extremely sharp, please be careful when using it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Highly recommend for the price
reviews.reviewText: I’m giving this knife a 5 star review with the caveat that I’ve only had it a couple days. That said, it is extremely sharp out of the box. It’s light and fits well in my wife’s hand. This is important for an older person or someone with arthritis. The quality of the blade seems good and for the price I’d highly recommend this knife. Even if I have to replace it in a year it would probably be worth it compared to having to sharpen a more costly knife. I’m actually going to buy another as the price is almost inconsequential.Edit. I’ve bought another one and plan on a third. I have no idea how long this blade will retain its edge but whether cutting onions or frozen sausage this knife makes it easy.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice and sharp
reviews.reviewText: These are nice and sharp little knives with very thin blades.They're perfect for slicing tomatoes, and the tomatoes don't stick to them since the blades have the patterned holes in them.They aren't the strongest knives in the world though. I mean, I wouldn't try to crack open a watermelon with them. Although they'd probably handle it, it seems like that kind of thing would wear them out pretty quickly.Overall they're great for tomatoes, peppers, radishes, etc. All the smaller stuff. I really like them.
